\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 53. P. asplenifolia} Floerke ex Willd., {\i Sp. Pl.}{\b  3}: 208 (1800). Stem 2-8 cm, ascending to erect, glabrous below, lanate above with reddish hairs. Leaves glabrous, narrowly lanceolate, pinnatisect with ovate-lanceolate, crenate to pinnatifid segments. Flowers 2-5(-8) in a dense, capitate raceme; bracts pinnatifid, reddish-lanate, about as long as calyx. Calyx villous-lanate with reddish hairs; teeth short, foliose, pinnatifid. Corolla up to 17 mm, pinkish-red; tube equalling calyx; lower lip glabrous. Capsule oblong-ovoid, rostrate, exceeding calyx. 2n = 16.{\i  Alpine pastures and screes; calcifuge. • E. Alps.} Au He It.
